text: Five ships of the Royal Navy have been named Sharpshooter (or Sharp Shooter). * was a 12-gun brig launched in 1805. She was sold in 1816. * was an iron screw gunvessel launched in 1846. She was sold in 1869. * was a torpedo gunboat launched in 1888. In 1912 she was renamed and reduced to harbour service. Sold in 1922 and broken up. * was an launched in 1917 and scrapped in 1927. * was a launched in 1936. Converted to a survey ship and renamed Shackleton in 1953 she was scrapped in 1965.
